dismissalText.commentary: David Wiese run out (McClenaghan) 14 (8b 0x4 2x6 12m) SR: 175

dismissalComment.html: two in a two, McClenaghan finishes it off in style! Wiese went for the heave and got an inside edge onto his pad, the ball was close to the pitch on the leg side and MM quickly picked it up, turned around and shattered the stumps at the non-striker's end with a direct hit. Two sixes to start the over, two run outs to end it

dismissalText.commentary: Tom Latham lbw b Philander 60 (80b 4x4 1x6 134m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: another one, Philander removes the well-set Latham! The batsman shuffled across a bit, Philander pitched it on length on middle and the ball was nipping in, struck him right in front of the stumps and the finger went up, looked plumb

dismissalText.commentary: Ish Sodhi run out (Philander/Rabada) 0 (0b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gone, it is all over. Very very interesting cricket from NZ. Milne drills past the bowler and they run through for one. But NZ's batsmen aren't satisfied with just the one though. The mid-off fielder is quick to his right to keep it in and gets in a quick throw to Rabada. Just a slight misfield from Philander at mid-off and Sodhi comes back for two. He is well short though and that means South Africa take a 1-0 lead in the series.

commentPreTextItems.html: Basanta: "whom to support at this stage of the game? thoughts are becoming pendulum"

commentTextItems.html: gone, it is all over. Very very interesting cricket from NZ. Milne drills past the bowler and they run through for one. But NZ's batsmen aren't satisfied with just the one though. The mid-off fielder is quick to his right to keep it in and gets in a quick throw to Rabada. Just a slight misfield from Philander at mid-off and Sodhi comes back for two. He is well short though and that means South Africa take a 1-0 lead in the series.

commentPostTextItems.html: 8.50pm Right, then. That is it from me for this first ODI. Do join us for the second ODI between these two sides on Sunday. Until then, ciao.

8.30pm Well, what a match to begin. New Zealand will be distraught with that chase. They had it for major chunks of that innings, but lost too many wickets far too quickly. A brief few overs in the middle claimed three-four wickets, which in hindsight was the turning point of the game. South Africa were excellent for lots of that bowling innings but were unnaturally poor for a lot of time too. Their fielding is a point of concern, more than a few catches were dropped. But more importantly, they found a way to win.\

Hashim Amla is the Man of the Match. "Myself and Morne found that it was quite hard initially. We found some runs early which released the pressure. I thought 250 was defendable at the interval. Rilee is an exceptional player and we learn from each other."

AB de Villiers: "Very happy with the win, always happy with the win. We played well in patches but some very poor cricket in between. We didn't hit our straps and we need to do that on Sunday. Amazing set up by Hash again. I thought it was hard to bat at the end, the ball got a little soft at the end, I thought we should have won by a bigger margin. I was a bit worried about our energy, but it happens when we have some new faces. Reverse swing went away as we changed the ball but we adapted well.

Kane Williamson: "The way the boys stuck at it with the ball was a good effort. It's always a fine line with white ball cricket. If we could have carried a partnership or two, it would have been interesting. But we were outplayed. Some areas to touch on and SA are a top side and we had to be at our best to beat them. It's always about adapting."
Mumble: "Both teams looked determined to snatch defeat from the jaws of victory - but it made for entertaining cricket. Good game. "

commentTextItems.html: gone this time. Cleaned him up. Cross seamed delivery on off stump on a fuller length, MM makes room to try and drive over cover. But misses. The off stump is broken and NZ are 9 down. Very interesting shot.

commentTextItems.html: and some more runs. Dale Steyn goes short, bouncer on middle and leg. MM gets a little bat of glove on it which agonisingly lobs over Morne van Wky for four more.

low full toss outside off, slogged to deep midwicket where they decide to come back for a suicidal second run. The throw is slightly wide and van Wyk collects cleanly but fails to hit the stumps. Should have been out
in the hitting arc again. But outside off, MM misses the slog-heave again
excellent yorker but NZ get two. Inside-edged just past the stumps. Runs down towards fine leg. But they scamper through for two.

commentPreTextItems.html: So just 10 runs per over required. Very gettable for NZ. SA will need a wicket to calm their nerves. Dale Steyn is back to get that wicket

commentTextItems.html: angled across the heaving bat of MM. McClenaghan moves across but misses the slog
banged in halfway down the track again, heaved away to the right of de Villiers at long-on. They come back for two

commentTextItems.html: lower full toss, mistimed off the front foot towards mid-off
slower offcutter once more and cracked away off the front foot way over deep midwicket. Massive six. Interesting times.
shorter offcutter on off stump. Bouncer. Pulled off the front foot to deep square leg
quick delivery this time, Milne swats to long-on with no timing. Just enough to get two though

commentPreTextItems.html: jayakanth: "can i trade that catch for behardien's drop during WC 15 semifinals." -- No, you can't.

commentTextItems.html: another boundary. Slower offcutter on middle and leg, Milne helps it along it s way past short fine leg for another boundary
googly again, van Wyk doesn't pick it either. MM misses his sweep and luckily too because he earned his side four extras

fuller googly again outside off, MM swats it off the front foot to long-on
yorker on middle, drilled back to the bowler

commentPreTextItems.html: 54 off 30 balls, still very gettable but way too many wickets have fallen

commentTextItems.html: googly first up, outside off. McClenaghan has no idea and is beaten by miles

dismissalComment.html: holes out to deep midwicket, AB is gone, I repeat, AB is gone! Milne pitched it short, AB pulled but didn't middle it again and it was an easy catch for Latham in the deep, even though he was a few yards in

dismissalText.commentary: Hashim Amla b Milne 124 (126b 13x4 3x6 193m) SR: 98.41

dismissalComment.html: 142kph, tries the block hole, gets the wicket and Amla gone too! It was pretty straight on the off stump, Amla opened up to find the gap on the off side but only got a thin edge, there was some reverse swing, before the ball knocked the bottom of middle stump

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: David Miller c Milne b Neesham 14 (13b 1x4 0x6 21m) SR: 107.69

dismissalComment.html: finally a catch has been taken, Miller falls too! There was room on off, it was an offcutter, Miller swished at it to find backward point

dismissalText.commentary: Farhaan Behardien run out (†Ronchi/McClenaghan) 15 (10b 1x4 1x6 27m) SR: 150

dismissalComment.html: keeps the short balls going, batsman misses and tries another bye but MM hits the stumps at bowler's end. Behardien also missed the pull, Wiese had already taken off for the single but Ronchi was quick enough to throw the ball to the bowler who did the rest

headshotImage.caption: David Wiese player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: David Wiese player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: David Wiese player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: David Wiese player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: David Wiese run out (McClenaghan) 14 (8b 0x4 2x6 12m) SR: 175

dismissalComment.html: two in a two, McClenaghan finishes it off in style! Wiese went for the heave and got an inside edge onto his pad, the ball was close to the pitch on the leg side and MM quickly picked it up, turned around and shattered the stumps at the non-striker's end with a direct hit. Two sixes to start the over, two run outs to end it

dismissalText.commentary: Tom Latham lbw b Philander 60 (80b 4x4 1x6 134m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: another one, Philander removes the well-set Latham! The batsman shuffled across a bit, Philander pitched it on length on middle and the ball was nipping in, struck him right in front of the stumps and the finger went up, looked plumb

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Ronchi c Amla b Steyn 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: gone this time, though. What a start this. Another gem of a delivery. In the corridor, moving away from Ronchi who can't do much with that other than poke at it. He gets a thick outside edge, and Amla at first slip takes a good, low catch. The umpires want to check if it has carried though. It has and he is gone

headshotImage.caption: Dean Elgar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Elgar player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c sub (D Elgar) b Imran Tahir
dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson c sub (D Elgar) b Imran Tahir 47 (69b 4x4 1x6 93m) SR: 68.11

dismissalComment.html: KW's gone, handed a catch to cover! He danced down the track after missing out on the full toss, timed the shot very well by taking it on the full, unleashed an inside-out drive but could not strike it over Elgar, who had to jump just a bit to grab it over his head with both hands

headshotImage.caption: David Wiese player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: David Wiese player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill c Miller b Wiese 25 (23b 2x4 1x6 25m) SR: 108.69

dismissalComment.html: Wiese has turned it around on debut, takes the wicket of Guptill after two fours! It was a slower offcutter, pretty full around off and the batsman lofted it down, probably seeing the length, but only found the safe hands of Miller at long-on. He was a few yards inside the boundary

dismissalText.commentary: Grant Elliott c Miller b Philander 4 (3b 1x4 0x6 6m) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: the slip comes in action, takes a good catch and that's the big wicket of Elliott! It was a touch back of length outside off, there was good bounce as Elliott looked to guide it to third man but only found Miller. They check for the no ball and there's some part of the heel behind the line

headshotImage.caption: Morne van Wyk player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Morne van Wyk player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: James Neesham c †van Wyk b Wiese 41 (41b 6x4 0x6 55m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: gone, what a massive wicket for SA. Neesham is gone. Wiese does the trick. Very clever slower bouncer on off stump, Neesham is through the shot much too early and gets a thick top edge which is joyously accepted by van Wyk. Cannot stress the importance of that wicket enough with respect to the match.

headshotImage.longCaption: Colin Munro player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Colin Munro player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Colin Munro player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Colin Munro lbw b Imran Tahir 33 (32b 3x4 1x6 64m) SR: 103.12

dismissalComment.html: 98 kph, get him this time. Another massive wicket. Wonderful bowling. Tahir flights the ball with no spin which dips very late on Munro and importantly, it is straight. Munro decides to reverse sweep or switch hit. He misses it altogether and is absolutely plumb. Easy decision for the umpire

headshotImage.caption: Kagiso Rabada player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kagiso Rabada player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nathan McCullum c Behardien b Rabada 10 (14b 1x4 0x6 20m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: what a catch Behardien. Stunning catch in the deep. Scintillating stuff. Short ball on middle and off stump, McCullum goes for the pull and executes half-decently. McCullum doesn't bother keeping it down though. Behardien runs around from square leg towards fine leg and completes a really really good catch.

dismissalText.commentary: Adam Milne not out 15 (12b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 125
Mitchell McClenaghan b Steyn 16 (13b 1x4 1x6 6m) SR: 123.07

dismissalComment.html: gone this time. Cleaned him up. Cross seamed delivery on off stump on a fuller length, MM makes room to try and drive over cover. But misses. The off stump is broken and NZ are 9 down. Very interesting shot.

headshotImage.longCaption: Kagiso Rabada player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ish Sodhi run out (Philander/Rabada) 0 (0b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gone, it is all over. Very very interesting cricket from NZ. Milne drills past the bowler and they run through for one. But NZ's batsmen aren't satisfied with just the one though. The mid-off fielder is quick to his right to keep it in and gets in a quick throw to Rabada. Just a slight misfield from Philander at mid-off and Sodhi comes back for two. He is well short though and that means South Africa take a 1-0 lead in the series.
